From: Tomato64 <noreply@tomato64>
Subject: [PATCH] cap SOLICIT/INFORMATION-REQUEST retransmit backoff

The OPNsense/RFC 8415 value for SOL_MAX_RT (and INF_MAX_RT) is 1 hour
(3600000 ms). With exponential backoff, if the ISP ignores the first few
Solicits at boot (upstream not ready yet), the retransmit interval can
balloon toward the 1h cap (256s -> 512s -> 1024s...), so the next Solicit
may not go out for 8-17 minutes. Users see IPv6 "take 7-10 minutes to come
up after boot".

The legacy tomato64/dhcpv6 (WIDE) base capped both at 120000 ms (120s), so
a missed Solicit was re-tried at worst every 2 minutes. Restore that cap to
keep IPv6 acquisition prompt at boot.

--- a/dhcp6.h
+++ b/dhcp6.h
@@ -73,10 +73,10 @@
 /* timer parameters (msec, unless explicitly commented) */
 #define SOL_MAX_DELAY	1000
 #define SOL_TIMEOUT	1000
-#define SOL_MAX_RT	3600000
+#define SOL_MAX_RT	120000
 #define INF_MAX_DELAY	1000
 #define INF_TIMEOUT	1000
-#define INF_MAX_RT	3600000
+#define INF_MAX_RT	120000
 #define REQ_TIMEOUT	1000
 #define REQ_MAX_RT	30000
 #define REQ_MAX_RC	10	/* Max Request retry attempts */
